	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>What can I do to survive in groups as a bard?</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Oct 4th 9:41 AM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'm playing a bard currently at level 25 and I have one big question to the higher leved bards here...<br><br>When I group and more than one monster has been pulled, I allways end up taking the beats of all the monsters that are not current main target. This tends to shorten my bardlife expectancy quite a bit ... am I doing something wrong ?<br>I've seen the same situation with my 50+ alt character in both normal groups and on raids. If more than one monster is pulled or there is a glitch in the teamwork and members of the group/raid dies, it's ALWAYS the bard that goes down first. Even if it's just a minor slip ... if just one character goes down its almost always the bard.<br><br>I hope you have some good advice out there =)<br><br>/The Bardie</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>2 Replies</td></tr>
