	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Regardless of what everyone says, you can stop singing.&nbsp;&nbsp;Rogues are taught to stop attacking if they taunt the mob.  Is this wrong or ineffective?  No.  A dead rogue or bard is FAR more ineffective than a temporarily side-lined one.  Just stop, back up, and let the others (if you don't have the ability to) take care of them.  If it requires stopping your songs or attacks, then do so.  No one should make you feel guilty for trying to live through a situation.  Your songs being stopped for few ticks aren't going to ruin the groups chances between a glorious victory and a horrible slaughter.  If you get aggro'ed... stop singing.  Let the bards who continue singing die, while you live to sing yet another song a few moments later.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
